  "prompt": "Which country invented the sandwich?",
  "response": "The sandwich is named after John Montagu, the 4th Earl of Sandwich, an English nobleman. According to popular legend, he is credited with inventing it in the 18th century. The story goes that Montagu, an avid gambler, ordered his valet to bring him meat tucked between two pieces of bread so that he could eat without interrupting his game. Although variations of bread and filling combinations had existed long before, it was this tale that led to the naming of the sandwich. Therefore, the sandwich is often attributed to England.",
